A customer raised this up:
{quote}
We are mainly focused on end-user documentation so the problem is not quite so severe for us; most of the red links can be removed as they aren't relevant to us. However I did find some more that are relevant, buried away in the end-user documentation (eg re: embedding JIRA links), so it will be quite a chore to go through and find all of those. If I had to do this for the admin documentation as well, it would be a massive task, and this would rather make the idea of a local copy of the documentation impractical for such purposes.

The online instructions for all this were really quite misleading. They imply that 3 further workspaces (dependencies) are required, but in fact none of those 3 seem to be required by the 3.5 documentation, whereas many other workspaces are required but are not available. The red links wouldn't have caused us so much confusion if they had been documented in those instructions. And of course those red links could have been fixed by Atlassian before doing the XML export.

Along the way, I found a couple more aspects:

- 'nomarkup' and 'hide' user macros appear; obviously I could look those up and install them if required but that too is not documented in the instructions.
- In the case of the Sharepoint Connector Guide section, this uses an 'include' macro to include contents of another space, and I don't think that can be redirected to the online version in the way you described earlier. That's not a problem for us, because we don't use the Connector, but it could be an issue for anybody who does.

{quote}

